<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="exact-adj">exact <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ɪɡ'zækt/    美 /ɪɡ'zækt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-precise">1.★ <strong>精确的；准确的；严谨的 (precise)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>an exact copy of the painting 
那幅画的精确复制品</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>In the late 1700s, people did not know the <strong>exact time</strong> unless they were near a clock. 
18世纪后期，除非身边有钟表，否则人们不知道确切的时间。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>an exact scholar 
治学严谨的学者</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="to-be-exact">to be exact</h3>
<p>1.<strong>确切地说：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I read an article about paper, to be exact, about how much Americans use up each year. 
我读到一篇有关纸的文章，确切地说，是关于美国人每年用纸量的文章。</p></div></div>